WEBVTT

00:04.838 --> 00:05.805 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.839 --> 00:07.574 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.607 --> 00:11.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
President Trump
claims to be the victim of a
witch-hunt, as

00:11.177 --> 00:16.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Justice Department appoints
a special
counsel to investigate possible
Russian ties

00:16.950 --> 00:18.385 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to the Trump campaign.

00:18.418 --> 00:24.391 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then: We travel to Iran ahead of
a pivotal
presidential election there.

00:24.424 --> 00:31.031 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Plus: part two of our look at
how gender stereotypes
influence the jobs we take.

00:31.064 --> 00:33.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meet the football coach who
teaches second
grade.

00:33.733 --> 00:36.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HAROLD JOHNSON, Elementary
School Teacher:
Everybody looking like, hey what
you doing

00:36.703 --> 00:37.670 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
here?

00:37.704 --> 00:40.006 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You know, this isn't P.E. or
anything.

00:40.040 --> 00:41.908 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I'm just like, I know.

00:41.941 --> 00:43.810 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's reading and how to teach
kids how to
read.

00:43.843 --> 00:45.645 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's what I'm here for, to
learn that.

00:45.678 --> 00:48.515 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:48.548 --> 00:52.919 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:52.952 --> 01:05.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Trump
is rejecting
the need for an independent
investigator into

01:05.732 --> 01:08.268 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
his alleged ties with Russia.

01:08.301 --> 01:12.305 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's also again denying any
wrongdoing in
connection with Russia.

01:12.338 --> 01:18.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He spoke out today, as a newly
appointed special
counsel began looking into just
that.

01:18.344 --> 01:20.180 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
William Brangham begins our
coverage.

01:20.213 --> 01:22.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
Well, I respect the move, but
the entire thing

01:22.649 --> 01:24.651 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
has been a witch-hunt.

01:24.684 --> 01:27.821 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The
president's displeasure
with the naming of a special
counsel was crystal-clear

01:27.854 --> 01:31.391 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
at his joint White House news
conference with
the visiting president of
Colombia.

01:31.424 --> 01:36.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: There is no
collusion between
certainly myself and my
campaign.

01:36.362 --> 01:39.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I can always speak for
myself and the
Russians.

01:39.966 --> 01:40.934 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Zero.

01:40.967 --> 01:42.936 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I think it divides the country.

01:42.969 --> 01:47.707 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think we have a very divided
country because
of that and many other things.

01:47.740 --> 01:52.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: In a sudden
shift last night,
Deputy Attorney General Rod
Rosenstein appointed

01:52.846 --> 01:58.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
former FBI Director Robert
Mueller to investigate
Russian meddling in the
election, alleged

01:58.318 --> 02:03.857 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
collusion with the Trump
campaign and any
other related matters that may
arise.

02:03.890 --> 02:07.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Rosenstein said he acted to
restore the public's
trust.

02:07.427 --> 02:11.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That trust was certainly tested
in a series
of bombshell developments in
recent days.

02:11.965 --> 02:17.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First, there was the president's
sudden firing
of FBI Director James Comey last
week, then

02:17.403 --> 02:23.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
reports that Mr. Trump leaked
classified information
about the Islamic State group to
Russian diplomats,

02:23.676 --> 02:28.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and finally allegations that he
urged Comey
back in February to drop the
investigation

02:28.481 --> 02:30.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of Michael Flynn.

02:30.350 --> 02:34.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Flynn had just been fired as
national security
adviser for lying about his
contacts with

02:34.587 --> 02:35.989 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the Russians.

02:36.022 --> 02:38.691 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president was asked directly
about Comey
today.

02:38.725 --> 02:43.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
QUESTION: Did you at any time
urge former
FBI Director James Comey in any
way, shape

02:43.129 --> 02:48.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or form to close or to back down
the investigation
into Michael Flynn, and also as
you look...

02:48.434 --> 02:50.069 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP: No, no.

02:50.103 --> 02:51.871 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Next question.

02:51.905 --> 02:56.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
QUESTION: As you look back over
the past six
months or year, have you had any
recollection

02:56.543 --> 03:00.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
where you have wondered if
anything you have
done has been something that
might be worthy

03:00.613 --> 03:01.614 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of criminal charges?

03:01.648 --> 03:03.349 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I think it's
totally ridiculous.

03:03.383 --> 03:05.218 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Everybody thinks so.

03:05.251 --> 03:08.054 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Democrats had
for weeks
pressed for an independent
commission or special

03:08.087 --> 03:10.390 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
counsel, and most welcomed
Mueller's selection.

03:10.423 --> 03:12.091 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:12.125 --> 03:13.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER (D-NY), Minority
Leader: Mr.
Rosenstein has done the right
thing.

03:13.826 --> 03:18.565 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I applaud his decision for both
its correctness
and its courage.

03:18.598 --> 03:24.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I now have significantly greater
confidence
that the investigation will
follow the facts,

03:25.004 --> 03:26.806 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
wherever they lead.

03:26.839 --> 03:31.077 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Most
Republicans had resisted
naming a special counsel, but,
today, House

03:31.110 --> 03:33.613 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Speaker Paul Ryan and others
applauded the
move.

03:33.646 --> 03:35.348 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:35.381 --> 03:37.350 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker of the
House: The
appointment of a special
counsel, I think,

03:37.383 --> 03:42.555 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
helps assure people and the
Justice Department
that they are going to go do
their jobs independently

03:42.589 --> 03:45.592 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and thoroughly, which is what we
called for
all along.

03:45.625 --> 03:47.360 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:47.393 --> 03:50.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN CORNYN (R), Texas: Robert
Mueller is
perhaps the single most
qualified individual

03:50.430 --> 03:55.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to lead such an investigation,
in my view,
and he's certainly independent.

03:55.134 --> 03:59.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Mueller ran
the FBI for
12 years, taking over just days
before the

03:59.839 --> 04:04.010 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
9/11 attacks, and served both
Democratic and
Republican presidents.

04:04.043 --> 04:06.746 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Journalist Garrett Graff is the
author of
a Mueller biography.

04:06.779 --> 04:10.283 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GARRETT GRAFF, Journalist: Bob
Mueller's entire
history is as a tenacious
prosecutor.

04:10.316 --> 04:15.021 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so he will follow the Russia
investigation
wherever it leads.

04:15.054 --> 04:18.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the good news for Donald
Trump is, he's
also the only person perhaps in
America who

04:18.958 --> 04:24.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
could end up declaring that
there's no there
there, and having people believe
that.

04:24.197 --> 04:28.034 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Back at the
Capitol this
afternoon, Deputy Attorney
General Rosenstein

04:28.067 --> 04:32.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
briefed the full Senate in a
closed session
on the firing of Comey and the
handling of

04:32.672 --> 04:34.474 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the Russia investigation.

04:34.507 --> 04:39.412 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rosenstein wrote the memo that
the president
used as a basis to dismiss
Comey.

04:39.445 --> 04:44.550 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Missouri Democrat Claire
McCaskill says Rosenstein
acknowledged that the memo he
wrote on Comey

04:44.584 --> 04:46.853 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
wasn't, in fact, what triggered
the firing.

04:46.886 --> 04:48.788 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:48.821 --> 04:51.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CLAIRE MCCASKILL (D), Missouri:
He did acknowledge
that he learned Comey would be
removed prior

04:51.891 --> 04:53.526 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to him writing his memo.

04:53.559 --> 04:54.794 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
QUESTION: Say that again?

04:54.827 --> 04:55.795 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
He what?

04:55.828 --> 04:57.664 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:57.697 --> 05:00.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CLAIRE MCCASKILL: He knew that
Comey was going
to be removed prior to him
writing his memo.

05:00.600 --> 05:04.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Republican
Lindsey Graham
praised the Mueller selection,
but also voiced

05:04.904 --> 05:05.872 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
misgivings.

05:05.905 --> 05:07.674 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

05:07.707 --> 05:09.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LINDSEY GRAHAM (R), South
Carolina: You couldn't
have picked a better man to do
the job.

05:09.542 --> 05:14.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think most people in that
meeting are
generally OK with the idea of a
special counsel.

05:14.547 --> 05:19.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what they don't quite
understand yet is
I think this has really limited
what Congress

05:19.218 --> 05:20.753 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
can do.

05:20.787 --> 05:24.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All of this as
new revelations
surfaced about Michael Flynn.

05:24.123 --> 05:29.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The New York Times reports the
Trump transition
team knew Flynn was under
investigation weeks

05:29.829 --> 05:33.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
before the inauguration for
secretly working
as a paid lobbyist for Turkey.

05:34.000 --> 05:39.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The McClatchy News Service
reported that,
during the transition, Flynn
blocked a military

05:39.639 --> 05:43.576 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
plan against the Islamic State
that was opposed
by Turkey.

05:43.609 --> 05:46.145 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was later approved after his
ouster.

05:46.179 --> 05:51.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Reuters reports Flynn and
other Trump
campaign advisers had contact
with Russian

05:51.050 --> 05:56.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
officials at least 18 times
during the last
seven months of the presidential
campaign.

05:56.856 --> 06:01.227 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Meanwhile, the House
Intelligence Committee
became the latest congressional
panel to ask

06:01.260 --> 06:06.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for more documents on the ouster
of Comey
and his conversations with the
president.

06:06.432 --> 06:08.468 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
William Brangham.

06:08.501 --> 06:13.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we turn now
to our Lisa
Desjardins on Capitol Hill and
John Yang at

06:14.006 --> 06:14.974 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the White House.

06:15.007 --> 06:16.809 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lisa, I'm going to start with
you.

06:16.843 --> 06:20.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We were just hearing from those
senators as
they came out of the briefing
with the deputy

06:20.079 --> 06:21.047 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
attorney general.

06:21.080 --> 06:22.915 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What more are you hearing from
that?

06:22.949 --> 06:26.085 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Right, those
senators emerged
with one unified theme, that the
deputy attorney

06:26.119 --> 06:28.755 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
general was a very cautious man.

06:28.788 --> 06:33.226 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he, on many questions,
actually deferred,
saying he couldn't answer them,
that it was

06:33.259 --> 06:35.495 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
up to the new special counsel,
Mueller.

06:35.528 --> 06:39.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now, Judy, that left
Republicans, they said,
with a sense of confidence that
here was a

06:39.999 --> 06:44.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
deputy attorney general who was
trying to
remove politics and Congress
from this investigation.

06:44.670 --> 06:46.572 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Democrats, however, they were
frustrated.

06:46.606 --> 06:51.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They said they're worried that,
as this goes
forward, they may not get many
details about

06:51.711 --> 06:53.179 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what is happening with this
investigation.

06:53.212 --> 06:56.249 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Lisa, other
questions
the senators were asking today?

06:56.282 --> 06:58.084 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The big one.

06:58.117 --> 07:03.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They asked repeatedly, who told
Deputy Attorney
General Rosenstein to write that
letter about

07:03.256 --> 07:05.958 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
why FBI Director Comey should be
fired?

07:05.992 --> 07:07.126 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They asked him again and again.

07:07.160 --> 07:08.928 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And we're told he didn't answer.

07:08.961 --> 07:10.830 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So it's a question still in the
air.

07:10.863 --> 07:15.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, John, at the
White House,
they were fielding questions
about a new FBI

07:15.201 --> 07:16.169 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
director.

07:16.202 --> 07:17.403 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I know I was there.

07:17.437 --> 07:21.040 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president had a session with
television
news anchors.

07:21.073 --> 07:25.611 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But, clearly, one of the
questions on their
mind is getting to the choice of
this new

07:25.645 --> 07:26.612 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
FBI director.

07:26.646 --> 07:28.448 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: That's right.

07:28.481 --> 07:32.084 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And at a photo opportunity with
the Colombian
president, he repeated what he
told you and

07:32.118 --> 07:38.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the other anchors at lunch, that
he expects
to name a new FBI director very
soon.

07:38.124 --> 07:42.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, he doesn't say exactly what
that means,
if that's going to be as soon as
before he

07:42.562 --> 07:46.532 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
leaves on his first foreign trip
tomorrow
afternoon.

07:46.566 --> 07:51.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And aides say that he's holding
this rather
close to his vest, but he has
indicated that

07:51.804 --> 07:55.041 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Joe Lieberman is a leading
candidate.

07:55.074 --> 07:57.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lieberman said that this is a
bit of a surprise
to him.

07:57.944 --> 08:01.481 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He came in, spoke to the
president yesterday
afternoon.

08:01.514 --> 08:06.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said he didn't seek this,
that he had been
invited, he had been invited to
come speak

08:06.352 --> 08:09.455 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to the president just the day
before.

08:09.489 --> 08:15.261 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This wouldn't only be something
of a bipartisan
selection, but sort of a
pan-partisan selection.

08:15.294 --> 08:19.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was, of course, Al Gore's
running mate
on the Democratic ticket in
2000.

08:19.899 --> 08:27.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He ran for reelection after
losing the Democratic
primary as an independent in
2006, and then,

08:27.173 --> 08:32.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
2008, sort of broke with the
party, went to
the Republican Convention, and
endorsed John

08:32.845 --> 08:36.382 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
McCain against President Barack
Obama's reelection
campaign.

08:36.415 --> 08:38.084 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

08:38.117 --> 08:40.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Of course, Lieberman, a longtime
Democratic
senator from the state of
Connecticut.

08:40.286 --> 08:43.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, Lisa, what's the reaction on
the Hill
to this talk?

08:43.256 --> 08:44.223 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Right.

08:44.257 --> 08:46.092 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's another one of these
reverse worlds.

08:46.125 --> 08:49.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Democrats who would have
elected Lieberman
as vice president told me today
they're not

08:49.562 --> 08:51.397 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
sure he should be FBI director.

08:51.430 --> 08:55.268 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They said again and again they
think it should
be someone who has never held
elected offices,

08:55.301 --> 08:57.169 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
someone outside of politics.

08:57.203 --> 09:01.073 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Republicans, on the other hand,
say they love
the choice of Joe Lieberman.

09:01.107 --> 09:05.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
